1
00:00:00,766 --> 00:00:03,565
(The spring flowers are in bloom...)

2
00:00:03,566 --> 00:00:06,806
(and the clear waves are welcoming.)

3
00:00:08,666 --> 00:00:12,646
(We came to the port city of Mokpo.)

4
00:00:12,776 --> 00:00:14,005
- Hello.
- Hello.

5
00:00:14,006 --> 00:00:15,045
- Hello.
- Hello.

6
00:00:15,046 --> 00:00:16,545
- Did you see this?
- Hello.

7
00:00:16,546 --> 00:00:17,875
- Director Joo's hurt.
- Why?

8
00:00:17,876 --> 00:00:19,045
- What?
- Look at him.

9
00:00:19,046 --> 00:00:20,445
- What happened?
- What's that?

10
00:00:20,446 --> 00:00:21,585
- How come?
- He hurt his bones.

11
00:00:21,586 --> 00:00:23,415
- What is that?
- I knew something would happen.

12
00:00:23,416 --> 00:00:24,515
How did you get hurt?

13
00:00:24,516 --> 00:00:27,685
I was riding a bicycle and I bumped into a stone curb.

14
00:00:27,686 --> 00:00:29,825
He shattered his big toe.

15
00:00:29,826 --> 00:00:30,895
- Really?
- Oh, dear.

16
00:00:30,896 --> 00:00:31,896
What now?

17
00:00:31,897 --> 00:00:33,725
- Let's cancel the shoot.
- I'll try to recover.

18
00:00:33,726 --> 00:00:35,866
- We can't do that.
- You're hurt.

19
00:00:35,996 --> 00:00:37,765
Your toe must be cold.

20
00:00:37,766 --> 00:00:39,466
How did that happen?

21
00:00:39,836 --> 00:00:41,935
Too bad. How will you manage today?

22
00:00:41,936 --> 00:00:43,675
Weren't you on TV recently?

23
00:00:43,676 --> 00:00:45,206
- What? Me?
- Yes.

24
00:00:45,636 --> 00:00:46,805
- What do you mean?
- What TV?

25
00:00:46,806 --> 00:00:48,546
I think I saw something somewhere.

26
00:00:49,346 --> 00:00:51,146
- "Boss in the Mirror."
- You were on that?

27
00:00:51,246 --> 00:00:53,216
- No, Jun Hyun Moo.
- Yes.

28
00:00:53,346 --> 00:00:54,686
He won the Grand Award,

29
00:00:54,986 --> 00:00:56,815
and he handed out rice cakes to the variety division.

30
00:00:56,816 --> 00:00:58,616
- You appeared then?
- It was a brief shot.

31
00:00:59,456 --> 00:01:01,656
It used to be a dream of mine to be on 2 Days 1 Night.

32
00:01:02,386 --> 00:01:05,326
(Director Joo confirmed Hyun Moo's willingness to be on the show.)

33
00:01:05,896 --> 00:01:07,626
- Will he be here today?
- What?

34
00:01:07,896 --> 00:01:08,896
Is Hyun Moo here?

35
00:01:08,897 --> 00:01:10,165
I'm not that pleased...

36
00:01:10,166 --> 00:01:11,666
- to see him.
- Why not?

37
00:01:11,866 --> 00:01:13,936
My mom's hoping she can be a regular on the show.

38
00:01:14,606 --> 00:01:16,975
- My mom...
- She got a huge response.

39
00:01:16,976 --> 00:01:19,205
(From looks to how they play, DinDin's just like his mom!)

40
00:01:19,206 --> 00:01:21,806
(DinDin's mom is a great cook and she's an angel at heart.)

41
00:01:22,276 --> 00:01:24,876
(His cute mom did well on the program.)

42
00:01:24,976 --> 00:01:26,815
Our ratings was the highest for that time slot.

43
00:01:26,816 --> 00:01:28,545
- I heard. No way.
- Yes.

44
00:01:28,546 --> 00:01:30,515
- Your mom was a great help.
- Yes.

45
00:01:30,516 --> 00:01:31,985
Ms. Kim Pan Lye. Ma'am.

46
00:01:31,986 --> 00:01:33,425
- Thank you again.
- Thank you.

47
00:01:33,426 --> 00:01:34,485
(We thank DinDin's mom.)

48
00:01:34,486 --> 00:01:36,296
If we film until tomorrow,

49
00:01:36,356 --> 00:01:38,426
I'll have spent five days this week with Se Yoon.

50
00:01:38,796 --> 00:01:39,825
Why that often?

51
00:01:39,826 --> 00:01:42,125
We went to a performance on the weekend.

52
00:01:42,126 --> 00:01:43,196
The radio show.

53
00:01:43,536 --> 00:01:45,165
I saw him more often than I saw my son.

54
00:01:45,166 --> 00:01:46,235
I have an update.

55
00:01:46,236 --> 00:01:47,765
I went abroad recently.

56
00:01:47,766 --> 00:01:49,065
- What for?
- Why?

57
00:01:49,066 --> 00:01:50,335
We had a concert.

58
00:01:50,336 --> 00:01:54,876
We held a concert in Vietnam with the Korean expats.

59
00:01:55,276 --> 00:01:57,445
- By 100 was sick.
- He was unwell.

60
00:01:57,446 --> 00:01:58,845
So it was just me and Shinji.

61
00:01:58,846 --> 00:01:59,846
- It was just KOYO.
- Yes.

62
00:01:59,847 --> 00:02:02,085
You must've sung By 100's rap.

63
00:02:02,086 --> 00:02:03,286
No, Shinji did.

64
00:02:04,316 --> 00:02:06,855
- Is Shinji that good?
- She sang and rapped.

65
00:02:06,856 --> 00:02:09,085
You made that busy person rap too?

66
00:02:09,086 --> 00:02:10,856
- What did you do?
- I did the choreography.

67
00:02:12,726 --> 00:02:13,926
That's why the choreography...

68
00:02:14,866 --> 00:02:17,165
- Even you think it's funny.
- I feel guilty.

69
00:02:17,166 --> 00:02:19,046
- That's impressive.
- I don't know the lyrics.

70
00:02:19,466 --> 00:02:20,736
The rap's too fast.

71
00:02:21,206 --> 00:02:22,976
He can't rap, it's too fast.

72
00:02:23,576 --> 00:02:25,175
It looks like you spent a great week.

73
00:02:25,176 --> 00:02:26,745
Does Mokpo bring anything to mind?

74
00:02:26,746 --> 00:02:27,922
- Well...
- Thin-legged octopus.

75
00:02:27,946 --> 00:02:29,305
- Octopus.
- Octopus.

76
00:02:29,306 --> 00:02:30,745
(Mokpo's chewy, firm thin-legged octopus is famous.)

77
00:02:30,746 --> 00:02:32,245
I'd love to have some jjolboktang.

78
00:02:32,246 --> 00:02:33,616
It's famous for blowfish.

79
00:02:33,846 --> 00:02:36,585
These two got here at the crack of dawn...

80
00:02:36,586 --> 00:02:38,456
- and had breakfast.
- Okay.

81
00:02:38,656 --> 00:02:41,055
Of all the breakfasts he had before any of our shoots,

82
00:02:41,056 --> 00:02:42,385
- this was the best.
- It was.

83
00:02:42,386 --> 00:02:43,455
- We...
- The kimchi was insane.

84
00:02:43,456 --> 00:02:45,016
We walked into whatever diner was open.

85
00:02:45,156 --> 00:02:46,625
- Seriously.
- It was so good.

86
00:02:46,626 --> 00:02:47,765
As soon as we tasted it.

87
00:02:47,766 --> 00:02:49,512
- Beef bone soup.
- We weren't even filming,

88
00:02:49,536 --> 00:02:51,336
- and we exclaimed loudly.
- Really?

89
00:02:51,596 --> 00:02:53,605
- It was really good.
- You scored.

90
00:02:53,606 --> 00:02:54,835
As we ate...

91
00:02:54,836 --> 00:02:56,065
(Moved by the taste of Mokpo)

92
00:02:56,066 --> 00:02:57,075
You should try it.

93
00:02:57,076 --> 00:02:59,305
- Of all the places in Jeolla.
- Yes.

94
00:02:59,306 --> 00:03:00,405
- The food.
- Mokpo...

95
00:03:00,406 --> 00:03:01,445
You can eat anywhere.

96
00:03:01,446 --> 00:03:02,975
- It's harder to find bland food.
- Yes.

97
00:03:02,976 --> 00:03:04,815
That must be true. Wherever you go...

98
00:03:04,816 --> 00:03:06,486
- The kimchi and stuff is great.
- Yes.

99
00:03:06,916 --> 00:03:08,616
Do we get lots of food today?

100
00:03:09,016 --> 00:03:10,785
Mokpo is famous for thin-legged octopus,

101
00:03:10,786 --> 00:03:12,155
- as you said.
- The octopus.

102
00:03:12,156 --> 00:03:14,255
As well as skate, brown croaker, silver pomfret.

103
00:03:14,256 --> 00:03:15,586
The nine tastes of Mokpo...

104
00:03:16,156 --> 00:03:18,225
mixed with the seasoning of the southern region.

105
00:03:18,226 --> 00:03:20,025
(The seasoning of the southern region)

106
00:03:20,026 --> 00:03:22,025
It's the place to come to enjoy food.

107
00:03:22,026 --> 00:03:23,672
- It's on the rise.
- It's becoming popular.

108
00:03:23,696 --> 00:03:27,235
Today, we'll go on a trip to enjoy the tastes of Mokpo.

109
00:03:27,236 --> 00:03:28,765
(Enjoy the tastes of Mokpo.)

110
00:03:28,766 --> 00:03:30,675
- Good food.
- That's happiness.

111
00:03:30,676 --> 00:03:32,675
We can relax and eat a lot.

112
00:03:32,676 --> 00:03:33,906
- Yes.
- Right.

113
00:03:34,206 --> 00:03:35,605
- So...
- So?

114
00:03:35,606 --> 00:03:37,446
Today, you won't be on your own.

115
00:03:38,116 --> 00:03:40,886
You'll be joined by some friends who are...

116
00:03:41,586 --> 00:03:43,955
- especially suited for this trip.
- "Some friends?"

117
00:03:43,956 --> 00:03:46,385
- Are they heavy eaters?
- "Some friends?"

118
00:03:46,386 --> 00:03:48,156
Is it Tzuyang and Heebab?

119
00:03:48,486 --> 00:03:49,655
Tzuyang?

120
00:03:49,656 --> 00:03:52,626
Hey, Hyun Moo... He does... What's it called?

121
00:03:52,926 --> 00:03:54,466
- That eating show.
- "Moo No Plan."

122
00:03:54,596 --> 00:03:55,965
- We have many guests?
- Is it them?

123
00:03:55,966 --> 00:03:57,165
- Today's travel companions.
- They're here.

124
00:03:57,166 --> 00:03:58,665
- For real?
- Let's meet them.

125
00:03:58,666 --> 00:03:59,666
Are they behind us?

126
00:03:59,667 --> 00:04:00,705
Come on out!

127
00:04:00,706 --> 00:04:02,106
Where are they coming from?

128
00:04:02,636 --> 00:04:03,735
Where are they?

129
00:04:03,736 --> 00:04:05,505
(Walking up from a distance)

130
00:04:05,506 --> 00:04:06,946
They look like guys.

131
00:04:07,246 --> 00:04:08,406
There are two people.

132
00:04:09,716 --> 00:04:12,116
- They're pretty heavy-set.
- I'm a bit scared.

133
00:04:13,086 --> 00:04:14,645
The one on the right looks foreign.

134
00:04:14,646 --> 00:04:15,686
I can't see.

135
00:04:17,356 --> 00:04:18,985
(Glass floor that shows the sea)

136
00:04:18,986 --> 00:04:20,256
- Watch out.
- Shoot.

137
00:04:20,526 --> 00:04:22,756
- Hey.
- I really need to hang on.

138
00:04:23,026 --> 00:04:24,295
It's slippery. Be careful.

139
00:04:24,296 --> 00:04:25,495
(The guy in purple is a coward.)

140
00:04:25,496 --> 00:04:26,695
- Who is it?
- I don't see anyone.

141
00:04:26,696 --> 00:04:27,725
- Who is it?
- I don't see their faces.

142
00:04:27,726 --> 00:04:29,836
They don't have any facial features.

143
00:04:30,266 --> 00:04:32,766
- I can't see any features.
- I can't tell.

144
00:04:33,006 --> 00:04:34,965
- They don't have features.
- Who are they?

145
00:04:34,966 --> 00:04:37,106
They look like two rolls of gimbap.

146
00:04:37,676 --> 00:04:40,006
- What the heck?
- Gosh.

147
00:04:40,676 --> 00:04:42,075
It's Ho Young.

148
00:04:42,076 --> 00:04:44,176
(These two!)

149
00:04:45,546 --> 00:04:46,685
(Studied at Osaka's Tsuji Culinary Institute, )

150
00:04:46,686 --> 00:04:48,322
(one of the world's top 3 cooking schools)

151
00:04:48,346 --> 00:04:51,216
(Jung Ho Young, the pioneer of Japanese cuisine)

152
00:04:52,586 --> 00:04:53,925
(Graduated Kitchen Academy Hollywood with honors...)

153
00:04:53,926 --> 00:04:55,606
(and was crowned Asia's Star Chef in 2010)

154
00:04:55,756 --> 00:04:58,656
(Sam Kim, the saint of Italian dining)

155
00:04:59,196 --> 00:05:01,996
(They appeared together on a cooking survival show.)

156
00:05:02,196 --> 00:05:04,166
(I wish someone would keep pushing this down.)

157
00:05:04,396 --> 00:05:05,695
(Their chemistry and friendship...)

158
00:05:05,696 --> 00:05:07,206
(took over social media.)

159
00:05:09,006 --> 00:05:11,206
- Hello.
- Hello.

160
00:05:11,736 --> 00:05:14,375
- Hello.
- Hello.

161
00:05:14,376 --> 00:05:15,675
- Hello.
- Welcome.

162
00:05:15,676 --> 00:05:17,845
You appeared a while ago, didn't you?

163
00:05:17,846 --> 00:05:19,685
Yes. That was nine years ago.

164
00:05:19,686 --> 00:05:21,146
Nine years ago?

165
00:05:21,346 --> 00:05:22,955
- You've gotten bigger.
- Yes.

166
00:05:22,956 --> 00:05:25,615
- You got bigger.
- I haven't been running as much.

167
00:05:25,616 --> 00:05:27,126
(I ran a bit less and I got bigger.)

168
00:05:27,756 --> 00:05:29,185
- In the center.
- Everyone.

169
00:05:29,186 --> 00:05:30,955
Joining us for 2 days and 1 night...

170
00:05:30,956 --> 00:05:32,155
are best friends and chefs...

171
00:05:32,156 --> 00:05:34,165
Jung Ho Young and Sam Kim.

172
00:05:34,166 --> 00:05:35,796
Hello, everyone.

173
00:05:35,896 --> 00:05:38,066
Hi, I'm Jung Ho Young. Pleased to meet you.

174
00:05:38,766 --> 00:05:40,305
Why are you like this?

175
00:05:40,306 --> 00:05:41,936
- Are you shy?
- Actually,

176
00:05:42,166 --> 00:05:44,835
being on an incredible program like this...

177
00:05:44,836 --> 00:05:46,006
- No.
- Not at all.

178
00:05:46,206 --> 00:05:48,076
- You deserve to be on.
- I'm tearing up.

179
00:05:48,706 --> 00:05:49,945
(Don't be so humble.)

180
00:05:49,946 --> 00:05:51,815
People consult you a lot.

181
00:05:51,816 --> 00:05:54,516
Se Yoon and I are kind of...

182
00:05:55,146 --> 00:05:57,255
Can I call him "Ho Young?"

183
00:05:57,256 --> 00:05:59,016
- Yes.
- We're kind of close.

184
00:05:59,216 --> 00:06:00,585
- With me...
- You run together.

185
00:06:00,586 --> 00:06:01,985
- There's a running crew...
- They jog.

186
00:06:01,986 --> 00:06:03,296
Called Gungsirung Gungsirun.

187
00:06:03,426 --> 00:06:06,226
And Se Yoon met him while volunteering.

188
00:06:06,526 --> 00:06:08,025
A few people got together...

189
00:06:08,026 --> 00:06:09,465
and he was a huge help.

190
00:06:09,466 --> 00:06:12,095
We go places and cook for people.

191
00:06:12,096 --> 00:06:13,165
- That's great.
- Yes.

192
00:06:13,166 --> 00:06:14,235
- Please say hi.
- Okay.

193
00:06:14,236 --> 00:06:16,336
Hello. I'm Chef Sam Kim.

194
00:06:16,406 --> 00:06:18,636
I'm back after nine years.

195
00:06:19,676 --> 00:06:21,075
I feel a bit emotional.

196
00:06:21,076 --> 00:06:22,376
- Gosh.
- "After nine years?"

197
00:06:22,576 --> 00:06:24,275
- He was on the show nine years ago.
- Yes.

198
00:06:24,276 --> 00:06:25,276
Oh, really?

199
00:06:25,277 --> 00:06:26,445
- You were on before?
- Three times, he said.

200
00:06:26,446 --> 00:06:28,385
- Three times?
- I came on three times.

201
00:06:28,386 --> 00:06:30,085
When? Jong Min doesn't seem to remember.

202
00:06:30,086 --> 00:06:31,155
- No.
- Right.

203
00:06:31,156 --> 00:06:32,755
- I remember him.
- Tell us when he was on our show.

204
00:06:32,756 --> 00:06:35,225
He was on our show twice during the third season.

205
00:06:35,226 --> 00:06:36,625
- Right.
- When was the other time?

206
00:06:36,626 --> 00:06:38,325
(He appeared on the show twice in 2018.)

207
00:06:38,326 --> 00:06:39,525
- Right.
- When was the other time?

208
00:06:39,526 --> 00:06:40,626
- Today.
- Today.

209
00:06:41,226 --> 00:06:42,226
It's been nine years.

210
00:06:42,227 --> 00:06:44,107
- When was that?
- What did you do on our show?

211
00:06:44,196 --> 00:06:45,296
I remember...

212
00:06:45,966 --> 00:06:47,605
working all day on the show the last time I was here.

213
00:06:47,606 --> 00:06:48,866
(I just worked 9 years ago.)

214
00:06:49,676 --> 00:06:50,705
- He cooked for us.
- He cooked for you.

215
00:06:50,706 --> 00:06:51,935
Yes, I cooked on the show.

216
00:06:51,936 --> 00:06:53,376
And Chef Sam Gim...

217
00:06:53,706 --> 00:06:55,105
- It's not Sam Gim.
- Right.

218
00:06:55,106 --> 00:06:56,345
- It's Sam Kim.
- Sam Kim.

219
00:06:56,346 --> 00:06:57,815
- It sounds like fresh dried laver.
- I'm sorry.

220
00:06:57,816 --> 00:06:59,175
- My pronunciation isn't good.
- Fresh dried laver.

221
00:06:59,176 --> 00:07:00,962
- Chef Sam Kim.
- That's the name of a singer.

222
00:07:00,986 --> 00:07:03,285
He wasn't sure whether or not he should appear on our show.

223
00:07:03,286 --> 00:07:04,955
- Why is that?
- But Chef Jung Ho Young...

224
00:07:04,956 --> 00:07:06,585
persuaded Sam to star on our show.

225
00:07:06,586 --> 00:07:08,185
It wasn't easy to get him on the show.

226
00:07:08,186 --> 00:07:09,555
- Gosh, no.
- Why not?

227
00:07:09,556 --> 00:07:10,855
Did someone on our show bother you or something?

228
00:07:10,856 --> 00:07:12,795
- No. It's nothing like that.
- Is that it? Okay.

229
00:07:12,796 --> 00:07:14,165
He said he had already been on this show.

230
00:07:14,166 --> 00:07:16,095
- What are you talking about?
- He didn't feel the need to return.

231
00:07:16,096 --> 00:07:17,395
- So...
- He'd already been on the show.

232
00:07:17,396 --> 00:07:18,995
- He was being arrogant.
- No.

233
00:07:18,996 --> 00:07:20,866
- No.
- "I've been on the show before."

234
00:07:21,606 --> 00:07:23,435
- I was busy with my restaurant.
- I see.

235
00:07:23,436 --> 00:07:24,805
- Of course, he's busy.
- I don't have a big team...

236
00:07:24,806 --> 00:07:26,176
at my restaurant.

237
00:07:26,306 --> 00:07:28,146
My absence would be noticeable.

238
00:07:28,346 --> 00:07:29,776
Did the sales at your restaurant...

239
00:07:30,016 --> 00:07:32,745
go up after "Culinary Class Wars?" I bet it got busy.

240
00:07:32,746 --> 00:07:35,015
His restaurant is fully booked for the next six months.

241
00:07:35,016 --> 00:07:37,362
- Really? They're all booked?
- We did get some reservations.

242
00:07:37,386 --> 00:07:38,455
How many people?

243
00:07:38,456 --> 00:07:40,332
You can make a reservation for my restaurant on the day of.

244
00:07:40,356 --> 00:07:42,325
- Gosh, no.
- Call me.

245
00:07:42,326 --> 00:07:43,555
- I went...
- It's...

246
00:07:43,556 --> 00:07:45,195
I went to Ho Young's restaurant...

247
00:07:45,196 --> 00:07:46,995
not long after the show ended.

248
00:07:46,996 --> 00:07:48,265
I couldn't even enter.

249
00:07:48,266 --> 00:07:49,425
It was so packed.

250
00:07:49,426 --> 00:07:50,795
- Was there a line?
- There was a long line.

251
00:07:50,796 --> 00:07:52,695
- Really?
