00:40:38,963 --> 00:40:40,262
- Lee Joon!
- It's Lee Joon.

1257
00:40:40,263 --> 00:40:42,332
Thank you!

1258
00:40:42,333 --> 00:40:45,002
(Shocked)

1259
00:40:45,003 --> 00:40:47,742
It's amazing that Jong Min caught the details.

1260
00:40:47,743 --> 00:40:49,072
That's because I ate the food.

1261
00:40:49,073 --> 00:40:51,583
- I wanted to do the same thing.
- He's scary.

1262
00:40:51,813 --> 00:40:53,743
We won't take it easy this time.

1263
00:40:54,983 --> 00:40:56,712
- They're scared now.
- I don't want to do it.

1264
00:40:56,713 --> 00:40:58,552
Letting him do it again...

1265
00:40:58,553 --> 00:41:00,183
- is the proper way.
- Right.

1266
00:41:00,283 --> 00:41:01,823
It's your choice.

1267
00:41:02,723 --> 00:41:04,893
(Thinking carefully)

1268
00:41:05,063 --> 00:41:06,623
Good luck to both teams.

1269
00:41:07,223 --> 00:41:08,293
Ready.

1270
00:41:08,593 --> 00:41:10,393
Start.

1271
00:41:10,433 --> 00:41:11,903
(Shouting)

1272
00:41:13,463 --> 00:41:15,309
(A disturbance operation with loud sounds from the start)

1273
00:41:15,333 --> 00:41:18,003
DinDin is eating now.

1274
00:41:20,403 --> 00:41:22,572
(They all are shouting to avoid quick-witted Jong Min.)

1275
00:41:22,573 --> 00:41:24,282
- DinDin just ate.
- Right.

1276
00:41:24,283 --> 00:41:26,142
- Just eat at ease.
- DinDin is out.

1277
00:41:26,143 --> 00:41:27,312
He's eating.

1278
00:41:27,313 --> 00:41:29,552
Just eat at ease.

1279
00:41:29,553 --> 00:41:32,453
(Jong Min is right that DinDin is a citizen.)

1280
00:41:32,983 --> 00:41:34,252
Seon Ho, shout for three seconds.

1281
00:41:34,253 --> 00:41:35,693
(Attacking Seon Ho, the next target)

1282
00:41:35,753 --> 00:41:37,293
(Shouting)

1283
00:41:39,063 --> 00:41:40,363
(Maybe it's not him.)

1284
00:41:40,393 --> 00:41:41,492
Chef Ho Young?

1285
00:41:41,493 --> 00:41:43,332
(Silent)

1286
00:41:43,333 --> 00:41:44,463
Ho Young?

1287
00:41:45,233 --> 00:41:46,303
What?

1288
00:41:46,903 --> 00:41:48,349
What's wrong with this small octopus?

1289
00:41:48,373 --> 00:41:50,373
- This is...
- What do you think is delicious?

1290
00:41:52,143 --> 00:41:54,473
It's good anyway.

1291
00:41:55,273 --> 00:41:57,883
- He's eating.
- It's so good.

1292
00:41:58,383 --> 00:41:59,383
Joon.

1293
00:41:59,384 --> 00:42:00,483
(Shouting)

1294
00:42:00,913 --> 00:42:01,953
Seon Ho.

1295
00:42:02,153 --> 00:42:04,753
(No matter how much they call, all they get in return is shouts.)

1296
00:42:05,983 --> 00:42:08,053
- All right.
- We have to hurry. Ho Young.

1297
00:42:08,453 --> 00:42:10,422
- Five, four, - Let's check the details.

1298
00:42:10,423 --> 00:42:13,092
Three, two, one.

1299
00:42:13,093 --> 00:42:14,093
Open.

1300
00:42:14,094 --> 00:42:15,192
(The meal is over.)

1301
00:42:15,193 --> 00:42:16,232
Oh, dear.

1302
00:42:16,233 --> 00:42:17,433
He's eating now.

1303
00:42:17,733 --> 00:42:18,763
He took it out?

1304
00:42:19,003 --> 00:42:20,363
He just ate it.

1305
00:42:20,773 --> 00:42:22,232
(I think he swallowed the broth.)

1306
00:42:22,233 --> 00:42:23,732
Didn't he swallow the broth?

1307
00:42:23,733 --> 00:42:25,072
No, I didn't swallow it.

1308
00:42:25,073 --> 00:42:26,802
- He ate the broth.
- He swallowed the broth.

1309
00:42:26,803 --> 00:42:28,913
- I didn't swallow it.
- You couldn't help it.

1310
00:42:29,943 --> 00:42:31,282
(Is Ho Young, who swallowed the broth, excluded?)

1311
00:42:31,283 --> 00:42:33,342
- He ate it.
- You swallowed it. You're out.

1312
00:42:33,343 --> 00:42:34,582
- He's out.
- It's just some liquid.

1313
00:42:34,583 --> 00:42:35,783
You swallowed the liquid.

1314
00:42:37,483 --> 00:42:38,622
He ate it.

1315
00:42:38,623 --> 00:42:40,553
He just got it out of the molars.

1316
00:42:40,653 --> 00:42:42,422
(Whatever!)

1317
00:42:42,423 --> 00:42:44,143
- I'm not supposed to do this?
- He ate it.

1318
00:42:44,193 --> 00:42:45,222
Did you get it out?

1319
00:42:45,223 --> 00:42:46,592
Don't you need dental floss? Are you all right?

1320
00:42:46,593 --> 00:42:48,093
He ate it.

1321
00:42:48,193 --> 00:42:49,293
He's just eating it openly.

1322
00:42:50,563 --> 00:42:52,032
(He can't stand the hunger.)

1323
00:42:52,033 --> 00:42:54,103
All right. I'll spare you.

1324
00:42:54,533 --> 00:42:56,703
It's not good that we have four members.

1325
00:42:57,233 --> 00:43:00,003
(Is Lee Joon, who picked up and put down the food, the Food Mafia?)

1326
00:43:00,443 --> 00:43:03,273
(Is it Seon Ho who kept mixing the food?)

1327
00:43:03,443 --> 00:43:05,642
I think we should ignore his words.

1328
00:43:05,643 --> 00:43:06,843
You go first.

1329
00:43:07,343 --> 00:43:08,959
- So we can ignore him.
- So we can ignore him.

1330
00:43:08,983 --> 00:43:10,082
I think...

1331
00:43:10,083 --> 00:43:11,122
(They ignore Sam Kim's guess with confidence.)

1332
00:43:11,123 --> 00:43:12,982
- It's Seon Ho.
- Seon Ho?

1333
00:43:12,983 --> 00:43:14,653
- Seon Ho.
- I also...

1334
00:43:14,893 --> 00:43:16,223
had the same thought.

1335
00:43:16,393 --> 00:43:17,662
Why? What makes you think so?

1336
00:43:17,663 --> 00:43:18,722
It's Seon Ho.

1337
00:43:18,723 --> 00:43:20,483
(He's eating well in the midst of all this.)

1338
00:43:20,693 --> 00:43:21,992
Do you see that they're silent?

1339
00:43:21,993 --> 00:43:23,463
Look. I think...

1340
00:43:23,633 --> 00:43:25,802
it's either Ho Young and Seon Ho.

1341
00:43:25,803 --> 00:43:26,932
- That's right.
- That's the energy.

1342
00:43:26,933 --> 00:43:28,232
- The energy.
- That's how it feels.

1343
00:43:28,233 --> 00:43:29,572
But Ho Young is eating now.

1344
00:43:29,573 --> 00:43:31,102
(Ho Young is eating now.)

1345
00:43:31,103 --> 00:43:32,103
He kept eating.

1346
00:43:32,104 --> 00:43:34,112
I thought he could be the Food Mafia. That means...

1347
00:43:34,113 --> 00:43:35,172
- I shouldn't have eaten it.
- So,

1348
00:43:35,173 --> 00:43:36,642
he can't be the Food Mafia.

1349
00:43:36,643 --> 00:43:38,612
So, it's one of these two. If you were to choose between them,

1350
00:43:38,613 --> 00:43:40,143
it's definitely Seon Ho.

1351
00:43:40,213 --> 00:43:41,652
- I agree.
- Exactly. I think it's Seon Ho.

1352
00:43:41,653 --> 00:43:42,982
Okay. Because of you...

1353
00:43:42,983 --> 00:43:44,283
Hang on. What are you doing?

1354
00:43:45,083 --> 00:43:46,622
(He's eating openly.)

1355
00:43:46,623 --> 00:43:47,922
He's eating openly.

1356
00:43:47,923 --> 00:43:50,862
(He has no intention to hide.)

1357
00:43:50,863 --> 00:43:52,462
- I already ate it.
- He thinks he's had enough?

1358
00:43:52,463 --> 00:43:53,722
Do you like the food?

1359
00:43:53,723 --> 00:43:54,863
- Yes, it's good.
- Okay.

1360
00:43:55,133 --> 00:43:59,503
All right. Who's the Food Mafia of Team Ho Young? One, two, three.

1361
00:43:59,863 --> 00:44:01,272
- Yoo Seon Ho!
- Yoo Seon Ho!

1362
00:44:01,273 --> 00:44:02,633
(Seon Ho is chosen as Food Mafia.)

1363
00:44:03,173 --> 00:44:04,403
What is the answer?

1364
00:44:05,003 --> 00:44:06,973
(Lee Joon with an unreadable expression)

1365
00:44:07,273 --> 00:44:09,372
(If Team Sam Kin gets it right, they win.)

1366
00:44:09,373 --> 00:44:11,343
- Please.
- One, two, three.

1367
00:44:11,983 --> 00:44:13,213
- Yoo Seon Ho?
- Yoo Seon Ho?

1368
00:44:13,243 --> 00:44:14,313
- It's correct.
- It's...

1369
00:44:15,183 --> 00:44:16,413
Did we get it right?

1370
00:44:16,783 --> 00:44:17,922
What's with Jong Min?

1371
00:44:17,923 --> 00:44:19,753
- How...
- We got it right.

1372
00:44:20,483 --> 00:44:22,222
He's horrible at acting.

1373
00:44:22,223 --> 00:44:24,322
Why? I did a good job.

1374
00:44:24,323 --> 00:44:25,492
Seriously.

1375
00:44:25,493 --> 00:44:26,923
(Feeling bitter)

1376
00:44:27,063 --> 00:44:28,733
As a result of the first mission,

1377
00:44:29,263 --> 00:44:30,832
Team Sam Kim won.

1378
00:44:30,833 --> 00:44:32,502
The winning team will get the meal of Mokpo small octopus...

1379
00:44:32,503 --> 00:44:34,033
(The meal of succulent small octopus)

1380
00:44:34,133 --> 00:44:36,833
and get to pick the main ingredients for the cooking showdown.

1381
00:44:37,773 --> 00:44:39,702
- Yes!
- You see,

1382
00:44:39,703 --> 00:44:41,842
we were going to take the food away right after the game,

1383
00:44:41,843 --> 00:44:44,142
but we'll let Team Ho Young have just one bite with chopsticks.

1384
00:44:44,143 --> 00:44:45,143
Just one bite?

1385
00:44:45,144 --> 00:44:46,242
You're not allowed to move the food.

1386
00:44:46,243 --> 00:44:48,052
No spoon. You must use chopsticks,

1387
00:44:48,053 --> 00:44:49,883
and you can only have one bite.

1388
00:44:50,283 --> 00:44:51,283
(Chef, please give us a tip on the best way to enjoy the food.)

1389
00:44:51,284 --> 00:44:53,552
- What's the best way to enjoy it?
- First, spread this.

1390
00:44:53,553 --> 00:44:55,922
You're having more than one sheet of dried laver.

1391
00:44:55,923 --> 00:44:56,953
Take three sheets.

1392
00:44:57,523 --> 00:44:58,962
Then, put some octopus from the octopus soup on top of it.

1393
00:44:58,963 --> 00:45:00,992
This will be their last meal of the day.

1394
00:45:00,993 --> 00:45:01,993
(The members are making a wrap, following the chef's advice.)

1395
00:45:01,994 --> 00:45:03,032
That looks good.

1396
00:45:03,033 --> 00:45:05,133
(His mouth is stuffed with a huge wrap.)

1397
00:45:06,363 --> 00:45:10,303
Please take away the food from Team Ho Young's table.

1398
00:45:11,043 --> 00:45:12,372
- They're actually taking it away.
- Look at the small octopus skewer.

1399
00:45:12,373 --> 00:45:13,373
Look at that.

1400
00:45:13,673 --> 00:45:16,473
(Yes, we're actually taking it away.)

1401
00:45:17,213 --> 00:45:19,443
(Jealous)

1402
00:45:19,483 --> 00:45:20,743
Seon Ho was so funny.

1403
00:45:20,953 --> 00:45:23,033
His facial expression was unnatural. It was obvious.

1404
00:45:23,653 --> 00:45:24,822
I'm a bad liar.

1405
00:45:24,823 --> 00:45:26,299
(The youngest member is still innocent.)

1406
00:45:26,323 --> 00:45:28,329
- Thank you for the food.
- Thank you for the food.

1407
00:45:28,353 --> 00:45:29,693
- Chef Kim, please eat.
- Okay.

1408
00:45:30,053 --> 00:45:32,133
What did you say was the best way to eat this again?

1409
00:45:32,663 --> 00:45:34,062
- Pick up a lot of...
- Try it my way.

1410
00:45:34,063 --> 00:45:36,432
- On top of 3 sheets of dried laver, - Did you say 3 sheets?

1411
00:45:36,433 --> 00:45:38,032
- spread chopped small octopus...
- Three sheets of dried laver?

1412
00:45:38,033 --> 00:45:39,033
Thinly.

1413
00:45:39,333 --> 00:45:41,733
Just like you spread rice when making gimbap.

1414
00:45:42,303 --> 00:45:44,173
- Oh, just like a sushi roll?
- Yes.

1415
00:45:44,243 --> 00:45:45,772
- Exactly.
- And stir-fried small octopus.

1416
00:45:45,773 --> 00:45:47,072
- Stir-fried small octopus.
- Stir-fried small octopus too?

1417
00:45:47,073 --> 00:45:48,972
Then, put small octopus skewer on top of everything.

1418
00:45:48,973 --> 00:45:49,973
Small octopus skewer.

1419
00:45:49,974 --> 00:45:51,482
- Is it the most seasoned one?
- Yes.

1420
00:45:51,483 --> 00:45:53,642
Since small octopus skewer is the most seasoned one,

1421
00:45:53,643 --> 00:45:55,653
you will taste the strong flavor first,

1422
00:45:56,313 --> 00:45:59,182
and then the chopped small octopus will mellow it out.

1423
00:45:59,183 --> 00:46:00,183
(The savory, chewy chopped small octopus...)

1424
00:46:00,184 --> 00:46:01,222
(mellows out the flavor in your mouth.)

1425
00:46:01,223 --> 00:46:02,783
- Small octopus skewer.
- Oh, I forgot.

1426
00:46:03,023 --> 00:46:04,423
That was tasty.

1427
00:46:04,963 --> 00:46:05,963
Can you help me with this?

1428
00:46:05,964 --> 00:46:07,044
He finished the whole bowl.

1429
00:46:07,193 --> 00:46:08,469
Right, he finished the whole bowl.

1430
00:46:08,493 --> 00:46:09,662
(They stuff a mouthful of Mokpo's flavors into their mouths.)

1431
00:46:09,663 --> 00:46:10,763
It's good.

1432
00:46:13,603 --> 00:46:14,872
(Yes, this is the taste I wanted to enjoy.)

1433
00:46:14,873 --> 00:46:16,033
- It's amazing.
- Indeed.

1434
00:46:16,503 --> 00:46:18,042
I see that being on this show makes you desperate for food.

1435
00:46:18,043 --> 00:46:19,963
(It makes you desperate even for just one bite.)

1436
00:46:20,503 --> 00:46:22,842
(Octopus soup will warm them up on this chilly day.)

1437
00:46:22,843 --> 00:46:24,812
- Oh, octopus soup.
- That was really good.

1438
00:46:24,813 --> 00:46:26,143
It must be so tasty as it's hot.

1439
00:46:26,943 --> 00:46:28,013
I see some octopus.

1440
00:46:28,983 --> 00:46:30,452
The broth is so refreshing.

1441
00:46:30,453 --> 00:46:31,583
It's very tender.

1442
00:46:31,923 --> 00:46:33,122
- The broth is amazing.
- I want to eat it too.

1443
00:46:33,123 --> 00:46:35,069
(The rich flavors of Mokpo's sea are hidden in the light, clean broth.)

1444
00:46:35,093 --> 00:46:37,863
(He drinks the broth right out of the bowl.)

1445
00:46:38,093 --> 00:46:39,523
This is good as well.

1446
00:46:39,723 --> 00:46:41,532
This small octopus skewer is so good...

1447
00:46:41,533 --> 00:46:42,862
as it has a smoky flavor...

1448
00:46:42,863 --> 00:46:44,383
- It has a smoky flavor, right?
- Yes.

1449
00:46:44,903 --> 00:46:46,763
And it's savory too. It's good.

1450
00:46:47,903 --> 00:46:49,032
(Laughing)

1451
00:46:49,033 --> 00:46:50,033
(What a simple description.)

1452
00:46:50,034 --> 00:46:51,842
- How was my description?
- It was precise.

1453
00:46:51,843 --> 00:46:53,603
(He's right about that, indeed.)

1454
00:46:53,703 --> 00:46:56,942
The variations on the same ingredient created diverse flavors.

1455
00:46:56,943 --> 00:46:59,912
The soup is nicely bland and savory.

1456
00:46:59,913 --> 00:47:02,253
And the stir-fried small octopus...

1457
00:47:02,353 --> 00:47:05,082
has a bit of a pleasant sour flavor and a soft texture.

1458
00:47:05,083 --> 00:47:06,122
It's sweet too.

1459
00:47:06,123 --> 00:47:07,722
The small octopus skewer...

1460
00:47:07,723 --> 00:47:09,322
- has a smoky flavor and...
- It has a strong kick.

1461
00:47:09,323 --> 00:47:11,322
Right. I think the dishes are meant to be eaten in a specific order.

1462
00:47:11,323 --> 00:47:13,662
You have these dishes first and then refresh your palate with the soup.

1463
00:47:13,663 --> 00:47:16,033
- It's like a course meal.
- That's right.

1464
00:47:16,193 --> 00:47:17,732
My, the broth is so refreshing.

1465
00:47:17,733 --> 00:47:18,863
It's so tender.

1466
00:47:19,133 --> 00:47:21,009
- The broth is amazing.
- I want to eat it too.

1467
00:47:21,033 --> 00:47:22,033
I'm jealous.

1468
00:47:22,703 --> 00:47:25,773
You can choose your ingredients while eating.

1469
00:47:26,773 --> 00:47:28,442
You know, Chef Kim said...

1470
00:47:28,443 --> 00:47:30,873
that he wanted halibut and Manila clams.

1471
00:47:31,613 --> 00:47:34,352
If he chose those just as he wanted,

1472
00:47:34,353 --> 00:47:35,612
- that'd make him look...
- Right.

1473
00:47:35,613 --> 00:47:38,683
- less competent as a chef.
- It's... You know...

1474
00:47:39,053 --> 00:47:40,822
Exactly. It'd mean he's not that competent.

1475
00:47:40,823 --> 00:47:42,492
- Like he can't cook anything else.
- Exactly.

1476
00:47:42,493 --> 00:47:43,652
- In fact...
- Like he can only cook those.

1477
00:47:43,653 --> 00:47:45,922
But I'm sure he can create great dishes with any of those.

1478
00:47:45,923 --> 00:47:48,132
He'd be so cool if he chose other ingredients.

1479
00:47:48,133 --> 00:47:49,792
(What will Team Sam Kim choose as their main ingredients?)

1480
00:47:49,793 --> 00:47:52,002
Then I'll go with halibut and Manila clams.

1481
00:47:52,003 --> 00:47:53,662
(Halibut, Manila clams)

1482
00:47:53,663 --> 00:47:55,532
Absolutely. We should go with those for the best taste.

1483
00:47:55,533 --> 00:47:57,233
Really? Are you serious?

1484
00:47:57,273 --> 00:48:00,072
- I guess that's really his limit.
- We'll go with those ingredients.

1485
00:48:00,073 --> 00:48:02,012
To tell you the truth,

1486
00:48:02,013 --> 00:48:03,572
I picked them because I wanted them,

1487
00:48:03,573 --> 00:48:05,782
but it was also to take away an ingredient that he could use...

1488
00:48:05,783 --> 00:48:07,242
- for umami.
- Right. That's the case.

1489
00:48:07,243 --> 00:48:09,612
- I knew it.
- To sabotage your opponent...

1490
00:48:09,613 --> 00:48:11,159
- by putting them in checkmate.
- Right.

1491
00:48:11,183 --> 00:48:13,152
If we had Manila clams,

1492
00:48:13,153 --> 00:48:14,522
- we could make pasta...
- They enrich the flavor of broth.

1493
00:48:14,523 --> 00:48:16,292
- with olive oil. It'd be tasty.
- That sounds yummy.

1494
00:48:16,293 --> 00:48:18,122
- What can we choose...
- Please pick one ingredient.

1495
00:48:18,123 --> 00:48:20,404
- What are you most confident with?
- How about flounder?

1496
00:48:20,693 --> 00:48:23,892
- I can make soup with flounder, - What do we need?

1497
00:48:23,893 --> 00:48:25,533
But it tastes best with Manila clams.

1498
00:48:26,663 --> 00:48:28,772
- How about silver pomfret?
- Braised silver pomfret?

1499
00:48:28,773 --> 00:48:30,149
I can make braised silver pomfret...

1500
00:48:30,173 --> 00:48:33,443
- in both Korean and Japanese ways.
- Let's go with silver pomfret.

1501
00:48:33,603 --> 00:48:36,249
