01:12:41,596 --> 01:12:44,536
We'll let the natural flavors of the ingredients do the talking.

2255
01:12:45,966 --> 01:12:49,736
(The unpredictable, chaotic spring meal battle)

2256
01:12:50,436 --> 01:12:54,076
(Who will be the winner of this intense cooking showdown?)

2257
01:12:54,506 --> 01:12:56,575
Spring Meal Battle: Flavor Versus Flavor...

2258
01:12:56,576 --> 01:12:58,716
with the best chefs in Korea.

2259
01:12:58,846 --> 01:13:00,385
(Jung Ho Young, Japanese cuisine owner-chef)

2260
01:13:00,386 --> 01:13:01,585
Let us begin.

2261
01:13:01,586 --> 01:13:03,156
- Yes!
- Yes!

2262
01:13:03,656 --> 01:13:05,755
Before the showdown begins,

2263
01:13:05,756 --> 01:13:08,085
each team will explain...

2264
01:13:08,086 --> 01:13:09,432
- the dishes they will make.
- Okay.

2265
01:13:09,456 --> 01:13:11,425
We'll make three dishes today.

2266
01:13:11,426 --> 01:13:12,995
Three dishes, not two.

2267
01:13:12,996 --> 01:13:15,936
Lemon butter grilled halibut.

2268
01:13:16,436 --> 01:13:18,165
- The second dish...
- Are we making too many?

2269
01:13:18,166 --> 01:13:21,636
- Too many.
- Manila clam and pen shell sujebi.

2270
01:13:21,836 --> 01:13:23,935
- Sujebi?
- That's a Korean dish.

2271
01:13:23,936 --> 01:13:25,435
You're shocked, right?

2272
01:13:25,436 --> 01:13:27,036
- The third one...
- Sujebi sounds nice.

2273
01:13:27,206 --> 01:13:29,946
Is the sirloin steak with shepherd's purse.

2274
01:13:30,446 --> 01:13:32,115
Gosh, their dishes sound a lot more intense than expected.

2275
01:13:32,116 --> 01:13:34,515
There's something that all dishes will have.

2276
01:13:34,516 --> 01:13:37,555
The ingredient that will be used mainly for all dishes is the garlic.

2277
01:13:37,556 --> 01:13:40,225
- The garlic.
- All three of us are married.

2278
01:13:40,226 --> 01:13:41,455
- We have our girlics.
- Right.

2279
01:13:41,456 --> 01:13:44,056
This is the name of our cooking.

2280
01:13:44,496 --> 01:13:50,066
- You're the only girlic I will love - You're the only girlic I will love

2281
01:13:50,096 --> 01:13:52,506
- I Love You, Girlic!
- I Love You, Girlic!

2282
01:13:52,866 --> 01:13:54,235
(He looks proud of his own dance moves.)

2283
01:13:54,236 --> 01:13:56,206
Gosh, that was neatly done.

2284
01:13:56,406 --> 01:13:58,906
- That sounds so old.
- That sounds so old.

2285
01:13:59,276 --> 01:14:00,945
(What about Team Ho Young?)

2286
01:14:00,946 --> 01:14:02,915
Explain the dishes for us.

2287
01:14:02,916 --> 01:14:04,775
I also prepared three dishes.

2288
01:14:04,776 --> 01:14:06,022
- Three?
- This is the first dish.

2289
01:14:06,046 --> 01:14:08,846
The webfoot octopus leg Sichuan tangsu.

2290
01:14:09,786 --> 01:14:11,055
The legs will be fried to be crispy...

2291
01:14:11,056 --> 01:14:13,725
