2378
01:17:14,406 --> 01:17:15,605
I'm confident in doing that much.

2379
01:17:15,606 --> 01:17:17,005
Is it done? Are there any heads?

2380
01:17:17,006 --> 01:17:18,846
- Quickly go for it.
- There aren't any heads.

2381
01:17:18,976 --> 01:17:20,406
- Go for it.
- Okay, then.

2382
01:17:20,576 --> 01:17:21,746
Flour.

2383
01:17:22,076 --> 01:17:23,516
I'll rinse it with some water first.

2384
01:17:23,676 --> 01:17:26,596
(The webfoot octopus is cleaned with flour to remove foreign substances.)

2385
01:17:27,086 --> 01:17:28,146
The knife.

2386
01:17:28,616 --> 01:17:29,716
Let's get this prepared.

2387
01:17:29,856 --> 01:17:31,516
Finish up with the braised dish.

2388
01:17:32,116 --> 01:17:34,256
- Stay calm!
- The sauce will be made.

2389
01:17:34,486 --> 01:17:35,555
(Washing the vegetables)

2390
01:17:35,556 --> 01:17:36,895
(Preparing the webfoot octopus)

2391
01:17:36,896 --> 01:17:38,095
(Setting up another burner)

2392
01:17:38,096 --> 01:17:39,225
Gosh, it's really cold.

2393
01:17:39,226 --> 01:17:40,425
(Team Ho Young looks stable from the start.)

2394
01:17:40,426 --> 01:17:41,526
Stay calm!

2395
01:17:42,766 --> 01:17:45,095
The head chef decided on our roles very well.

2396
01:17:45,096 --> 01:17:46,565
It wasn't that hard.

2397
01:17:46,566 --> 01:17:50,136
One would be a fool to make mistakes with these dishes.

2398
01:17:51,206 --> 01:17:53,706
(Chef Ho Young prepares the radishes.)

2399
01:17:54,276 --> 01:17:56,315
(The radish is sliced into half circles.)

2400
01:17:56,316 --> 01:17:59,045
(The skin is peeled off.)

2401
01:17:59,046 --> 01:18:04,016
(The edges are cut and shaped.)

2402
01:18:04,656 --> 01:18:07,056
(It gets put into boiling water.)

2403
01:18:07,156 --> 01:18:10,595
Our team is full of youth.

2404
01:18:10,596 --> 01:18:12,025
We won't be all over the place...

2405
01:18:12,026 --> 01:18:13,366
and we have great teamwork.

2406
01:18:13,426 --> 01:18:15,426
I believe our dishes will be made perfectly.

2407
01:18:15,496 --> 01:18:16,496
(Going all over the place)

2408
01:18:16,497 --> 01:18:17,536
Stay calm!

2409
01:18:17,636 --> 01:18:20,406
(Team Ho Young's weakest link appears.)

2410
01:18:20,736 --> 01:18:22,696
You're the only one who needs to stay calm, Joon.

2411
01:18:23,306 --> 01:18:24,375
(Joon has to prepare the aralia sprouts.)

2412
01:18:24,376 --> 01:18:25,506
There's no room.

2413
01:18:27,206 --> 01:18:29,045
(He starts preparing the aralia sprouts.)

2414
01:18:29,046 --> 01:18:31,716
(He does it in one corner.)

2415
01:18:31,946 --> 01:18:33,115
(Fried aralia sprouts and shrimp)

2416
01:18:33,116 --> 01:18:34,562
(The thorns on the outside are pushed out with the knife.)

2417
01:18:34,586 --> 01:18:35,716
Stay calm!

2418
01:18:36,116 --> 01:18:37,315
(His hands don't look calm.)

2419
01:18:37,316 --> 01:18:38,686
We're so short on time.

2420
01:18:39,186 --> 01:18:40,586
Gosh, my hands are cold!

2421
01:18:41,786 --> 01:18:44,025
I'll try to make it clean after rinsing it with water.

2422
01:18:44,026 --> 01:18:45,372
(The bad student and the good student)

2423
01:18:45,396 --> 01:18:47,366
It doesn't have to be prepared perfectly, right?

2424
01:18:48,266 --> 01:18:49,436
It has to be done perfectly!

2425
01:18:49,936 --> 01:18:51,056
It has to be done perfectly?

2426
01:18:51,136 --> 01:18:52,335
I think it will take too long.

2427
01:18:52,336 --> 01:18:53,882
(Will he be able to prepare at least one aralia sprout?)

2428
01:18:53,906 --> 01:18:56,276
(What about Team Sam Kim?)

2429
01:18:56,336 --> 01:18:57,935
- Move out of the way!
- Let's get the Manila clams.

2430
01:18:57,936 --> 01:18:59,136
Let's get the Manila clams.

2431
01:18:59,546 --> 01:19:01,206
Check the amount of water needed.

2432
01:19:01,506 --> 01:19:03,115
(Se Yoon starts making the sujebi dough first.)

2433
01:19:03,116 --> 01:19:04,846
I'll start with the dough.

2434
01:19:05,816 --> 01:19:08,085
We have double the amount of ingredients than the other team.

2435
01:19:08,086 --> 01:19:09,385
We will win no matter what.

2436
01:19:09,386 --> 01:19:11,616
It's time for Chef Sam Kim to take the win.

2437
01:19:11,756 --> 01:19:13,155
We will help him out a lot...

2438
01:19:13,156 --> 01:19:15,026
and secure our victory.

2439
01:19:15,326 --> 01:19:17,132
This needs more water, right? Should I carry on with the kneading?

2440
01:19:17,156 --> 01:19:18,525
Yes. Add some more water.

2441
01:19:18,526 --> 01:19:19,926
It needs more water, right? Okay.

2442
01:19:20,496 --> 01:19:24,796
(The ace member controls the dough based on the chef's orders.)

2443
01:19:24,836 --> 01:19:25,935
All right!

2444
01:19:25,936 --> 01:19:27,176
(Sam puts in the Manila clams.)

2445
01:19:27,336 --> 01:19:29,376
(Anchovies for the broth)

2446
01:19:29,976 --> 01:19:32,376
(He prepares the halibut right after that.)

2447
01:19:32,706 --> 01:19:35,206
(The scales get removed in a flash.)

2448
01:19:35,306 --> 01:19:37,515
I'm concerned as we have to make three different dishes.

2449
01:19:37,516 --> 01:19:40,346
I have to check every detail...

2450
01:19:40,546 --> 01:19:43,856
and I'm concerned that all dishes might become a failure.

2451
01:19:44,186 --> 01:19:46,685
But I think things will go well...

2452
01:19:46,686 --> 01:19:48,126
if the workload is distributed well.

2453
01:19:48,926 --> 01:19:51,156
(Jong Min is in charge of preparing the garlic.)

2454
01:19:52,526 --> 01:19:54,526
(He's still putting on his gloves.)

2455
01:19:54,566 --> 01:19:56,296
You have to tell me things as we work.

2456
01:19:56,466 --> 01:19:57,466
- Chef!
- Right.

2457
01:19:57,467 --> 01:19:59,836
- Tell me what to do.
- Right.

2458
01:20:00,306 --> 01:20:02,035
Please tell me what to do.

2459
01:20:02,036 --> 01:20:03,735
(Team Sam Kim's weakest link)

2460
01:20:03,736 --> 01:20:05,375
- Do I use the knife?
- Yes. Cut them one by one.

2461
01:20:05,376 --> 01:20:07,646
- Which knife should I use?
- Here. Use this.

2462
01:20:08,076 --> 01:20:10,357
- I need to cut the ends, right?
- Yes. Blend them after.

2463
01:20:10,516 --> 01:20:12,216
- Cut the ends and blend them?
- Yes.

2464
01:20:12,916 --> 01:20:15,085
(Slow)

2465
01:20:15,086 --> 01:20:17,126
Gosh, it takes a long time to cut off all of these.

2466
01:20:17,586 --> 01:20:18,956
Right. Keep them in water.

2467
01:20:19,016 --> 01:20:20,256
- Keep them in water?
- Right.

2468
01:20:20,626 --> 01:20:23,255
It will take too long. Just blend them.

2469
01:20:23,256 --> 01:20:24,355
- Sorry?
- Just blend them.

2470
01:20:24,356 --> 01:20:25,796
- After just a few of them?
- Right.

2471
01:20:25,826 --> 01:20:27,566
- We don't have time.
- Understood.

2472
01:20:27,726 --> 01:20:30,296
(Where's the olive oil?)

2473
01:20:30,396 --> 01:20:32,665
Did someone take the olive oil?

2474
01:20:32,666 --> 01:20:33,705
(Has the olive oil disappeared?)

2475
01:20:33,706 --> 01:20:35,565
Why is the olive oil missing?

2476
01:20:35,566 --> 01:20:37,112
(The olive oil is essential to a chef of Italian cuisine.)

2477
01:20:37,136 --> 01:20:38,336
Who took it?

2478
01:20:39,036 --> 01:20:40,176
The olive oil is missing!

2479
01:20:40,406 --> 01:20:43,646
(Someone secretly hides the olive oil before the start.)

2480
01:20:44,576 --> 01:20:47,116
(It's Chef Jung Ho Young.)

2481
01:20:47,886 --> 01:20:50,286
(He has adjusted to the wild after half a day.)

2482
01:20:50,756 --> 01:20:52,855
Here it is! Someone hid it there!

2483
01:20:52,856 --> 01:20:53,885
(It finds it behind the microwave.)

2484
01:20:53,886 --> 01:20:55,425
Things can't be hidden!

2485
01:20:55,426 --> 01:20:56,426
(Playing dumb)

2486
01:20:56,726 --> 01:20:58,926
(Team Sam Kim finds the olive oil.)

2487
01:20:59,196 --> 01:21:02,025
(The garlic, olive oil, and salt get blended together.)

2488
01:21:02,026 --> 01:21:03,135
Is this right?

2489
01:21:03,136 --> 01:21:04,666
(Everything feels new to him.)

2490
01:21:05,196 --> 01:21:08,236
(Let's blend it up.)

2491
01:21:08,566 --> 01:21:13,106
(The garlic has to be chunky.)

2492
01:21:13,576 --> 01:21:14,646
Gosh, I'm doing well!

2493
01:21:16,276 --> 01:21:17,876
How long must it be blended for?

2494
01:21:17,916 --> 01:21:19,016
Where? Let me see.

2495
01:21:20,346 --> 01:21:21,985
- That's enough.
- Enough?

2496
01:21:21,986 --> 01:21:23,115
That's enough.

2497
01:21:23,116 --> 01:21:25,556
(It's like garlic juice.)

2498
01:21:25,886 --> 01:21:28,426
(He's busy preparing the halibut and watching Jong Min.)

2499
01:21:28,726 --> 01:21:31,996
(He manages to get the halibut prepared.)

2500
01:21:32,056 --> 01:21:34,325
- Four minutes have passed!
- Gosh, this is insane.

2501
01:21:34,326 --> 01:21:36,565
Four minutes? I barely did anything.

2502
01:21:36,566 --> 01:21:37,672
(Four minutes went by in a flash.)

2503
01:21:37,696 --> 01:21:41,206
Chef Sam Kim must win this time, Se Yoon!

2504
01:21:42,006 --> 01:21:44,806
- Let's help him out!
- Shut that mouth of yours!

2505
01:21:45,206 --> 01:21:47,476
- Will you not talk?
- All right. Fine.

2506
01:21:47,606 --> 01:21:49,846
- Are you slacking off?
- This is driving me crazy!

2507
01:21:50,176 --> 01:21:52,715
All right, everyone! Everyone else must leave except number one!

2508
01:21:52,716 --> 01:21:53,945
What do I do?

2509
01:21:53,946 --> 01:21:55,715
Everyone else except for DinDin and Se Yoon must leave!

2510
01:21:55,716 --> 01:21:57,892
Everyone else except for DinDin and Se Yoon must leave!

2511
01:21:57,916 --> 01:21:59,386
- Peel the shrimp.
- Right.

2512
01:21:59,656 --> 01:22:01,776
- Use your time to peel the shrimp.
- Just go for it.

2513
01:22:02,186 --> 01:22:03,426
Make a cut on the belly.

2514
01:22:03,726 --> 01:22:04,925
You have time.

2515
01:22:04,926 --> 01:22:06,465
(The innards of the shrimp's back are removed with a toothpick.)

2516
01:22:06,466 --> 01:22:07,996
(The bitter part is removed.)

2517
01:22:08,566 --> 01:22:10,236
Shouldn't the radish be worked on first?

2518
01:22:10,396 --> 01:22:11,796
- I put in the radish.
- You did?

2519
01:22:12,366 --> 01:22:13,935
Gosh, just doing this takes up so much time.

2520
01:22:13,936 --> 01:22:16,305
- It's fine.
- It's fine. Take your time.

2521
01:22:16,306 --> 01:22:18,626
- Take your time. You're Lim Cheol.
- You're almost there.

2522
01:22:18,736 --> 01:22:19,805
I'll try to make the cuts as well.

2523
01:22:19,806 --> 01:22:20,945
- Okay! Let's go!
- Stay calm!

2524
01:22:20,946 --> 01:22:22,322
- Let's go!
- There's still a lot of time left.

2525
01:22:22,346 --> 01:22:23,715
How far have you gone with preparing the aralia sprouts?

2526
01:22:23,716 --> 01:22:26,946
The ones on the cutting board are the ones I prepared.

2527
01:22:28,846 --> 01:22:30,186
- You only prepared three?
- Yes.

2528
01:22:30,356 --> 01:22:31,815
You should prepare the aralia sprouts then.

2529
01:22:31,816 --> 01:22:33,125
- Right.
- Prepare the aralia sprouts?

2530
01:22:33,126 --> 01:22:35,386
I'm quite worried about Joon.

2531
01:22:35,586 --> 01:22:37,695
There's nothing done besides peeling the shell.

2532
01:22:37,696 --> 01:22:38,725
Right.

2533
01:22:38,726 --> 01:22:41,596
But the sunset over there looks beautiful.

2534
01:22:41,766 --> 01:22:43,966
- It looks amazing.
- Gosh, the sunset looks beautiful.

2535
01:22:44,096 --> 01:22:45,235
It's an amazing view.

2536
01:22:45,236 --> 01:22:47,266
- It's an amazing sunset view.
- Put that in!

2537
01:22:47,336 --> 01:22:48,966
The sunset is amazing!

2538
01:22:49,136 --> 01:22:50,476
The sunset looks beautiful!

2539
01:22:50,636 --> 01:22:52,105
It's pink!

2540
01:22:52,106 --> 01:22:53,822
(A wild cooking battle is happening at the Yellow Sea with a pink glow.)

2541
01:22:53,846 --> 01:22:56,945
- There's no time for the sunset!
- Hey!

2542
01:22:56,946 --> 01:22:59,146
- Who is up next?
- It's me.

2543
01:22:59,246 --> 01:23:01,885
- What about me?
- Get the aralia sprouts prepared.

2544
01:23:01,886 --> 01:23:02,915
Right.

2545
01:23:02,916 --> 01:23:05,015
Let's get everything prepared during our turns.

2546
01:23:05,016 --> 01:23:06,086
Right.

2547
01:23:06,656 --> 01:23:07,825
(Se Yoon is in charge of the sujebi dough.)

2548
01:23:07,826 --> 01:23:10,226
(Groaning)

2549
01:23:10,926 --> 01:23:13,426
