- The paper towel.
- Use the paper towel.

2602
01:24:54,796 --> 01:24:56,565
- Wipe them with the paper towel.
- Only the leaves.

2603
01:24:56,566 --> 01:24:57,942
- Only the leaves.
- Remove the moisture.

2604
01:24:57,966 --> 01:24:59,706
- Leaves?
- Yes.

2605
01:25:00,166 --> 01:25:02,805
- Leaves?
- Do you not know what leaves are?

2606
01:25:02,806 --> 01:25:04,136
- Only the green ones.
- What?

2607
01:25:04,206 --> 01:25:06,136
How do you not know the leaves?

2608
01:25:06,476 --> 01:25:09,076
(Feeling dizzy)

2609
01:25:10,846 --> 01:25:13,246
I didn't include Jong Min in my strategy from the beginning.

2610
01:25:13,746 --> 01:25:16,655
Jong Min was supposed to mince garlic and wash shepherd's purse.

2611
01:25:16,656 --> 01:25:18,316
I was going to do the rest.

2612
01:25:18,386 --> 01:25:19,725
Cut these off like this?

2613
01:25:19,726 --> 01:25:21,926
- Yes, only the green ones.
- The green ones.

2614
01:25:22,286 --> 01:25:23,525
Why can't you cut it? Are you weak?

2615
01:25:23,526 --> 01:25:25,195
- Like this? Okay.
- Yes. Just like that.

2616
01:25:25,196 --> 01:25:27,572
(Cut off the shepherd's purse leaves and put them separately.)

2617
01:25:27,596 --> 01:25:29,195
Hurry. We don't have time.

2618
01:25:29,196 --> 01:25:30,895
- How should I cut these off?
- Hurry!

2619
01:25:30,896 --> 01:25:32,365
- Hurry.
- It's been two minutes.

2620
01:25:32,366 --> 01:25:34,305
Half the time has passed.

2621
01:25:34,306 --> 01:25:36,205
- That's enough.
- Is this it?

2622
01:25:36,206 --> 01:25:37,236
- Stop it.
- Okay.

2623
01:25:37,476 --> 01:25:39,035
Taste the Manila clams.

2624
01:25:39,036 --> 01:25:40,076
Okay.

2625
01:25:40,446 --> 01:25:42,745
- Taste it.
- Many of them are open now.

2626
01:25:42,746 --> 01:25:44,976
Taste it. If it's too salty, add water.

2627
01:25:45,176 --> 01:25:46,656
Turn the stove off if it's not salty.

2628
01:25:47,386 --> 01:25:48,716
- My gosh!
- Is it salty?

2629
01:25:48,786 --> 01:25:49,886
I don't know.

2630
01:25:50,916 --> 01:25:52,585
- It just tastes good.
- Is it good?

2631
01:25:52,586 --> 01:25:53,955
- It's good.
- Then, it's okay.

2632
01:25:53,956 --> 01:25:56,056
- Turn it off, then.
- It's good. Okay.

2633
01:25:56,426 --> 01:25:58,425
- Bring that thing.
- Bring what?

2634
01:25:58,426 --> 01:26:00,125
- Did you bring it?
- Put it on here.

2635
01:26:00,126 --> 01:26:02,466
- Press the shrimp.
- Press them.

2636
01:26:02,526 --> 01:26:04,265
- Press what?
- The shrimp here.

2637
01:26:04,266 --> 01:26:05,835
- Do this first. These four.
- Okay.

2638
01:26:05,836 --> 01:26:06,836
(There he goes again.)

2639
01:26:07,006 --> 01:26:09,565
- Press it. You know how it feels.
- Yes. I know that.

2640
01:26:09,566 --> 01:26:11,475
- Okay. That's good.
- I know. I can do this.

2641
01:26:11,476 --> 01:26:12,835
- Go.
- Good. It's done.

2642
01:26:12,836 --> 01:26:14,875
Okay. I should massage them like this.

2643
01:26:14,876 --> 01:26:16,075
Like this.

2644
01:26:16,076 --> 01:26:17,776
- Can you hurry?
- No. I got this.

2645
01:26:17,946 --> 01:26:19,815
This isn't a sports massage.

2646
01:26:19,816 --> 01:26:20,845
(Laughing)

2647
01:26:20,846 --> 01:26:22,086
Just press it.

2648
01:26:22,546 --> 01:26:24,155
It's okay even if it bursts. Just press it hard.

2649
01:26:24,156 --> 01:26:25,316
Then, this will be...

2650
01:26:25,386 --> 01:26:27,025
- Just do it.
- Hurry.

2651
01:26:27,026 --> 01:26:28,225
- You should hurry.
- Stay quiet.

2652
01:26:28,226 --> 01:26:29,426
Then, skewer...

2653
01:26:29,486 --> 01:26:31,272
- It's done.
- the shrimp and the aralia sprouts.

2654
01:26:31,296 --> 01:26:32,395
Use the skewers.

2655
01:26:32,396 --> 01:26:34,326
- Stick it like this?
- Yes.

2656
01:26:34,526 --> 01:26:36,096
- I skewer it like this.
- No.

2657
01:26:36,566 --> 01:26:37,596
Like this.

2658
01:26:37,966 --> 01:26:39,835
- With the aralia sprouts.
- Horizontally?

2659
01:26:39,836 --> 01:26:42,206
- Here I go.
- That's it. Okay.

2660
01:26:42,766 --> 01:26:44,236
Stick it twice.

2661
01:26:44,406 --> 01:26:46,505
- One around the head.
- I'm sticking it.

2662
01:26:46,506 --> 01:26:48,375
- You should do at least this much.
- This is done.

2663
01:26:48,376 --> 01:26:51,115
- Skewer them on both sides.
- Like this.

2664
01:26:51,116 --> 01:26:52,375
One on the right, and one on the left.

2665
01:26:52,376 --> 01:26:54,145
- On the right?
- Put one more in here.

2666
01:26:54,146 --> 01:26:55,286
What? This part?

2667
01:26:55,516 --> 01:26:57,715
This part? Is this it?

2668
01:26:57,716 --> 01:26:59,215
- Yes. That's it.
- Okay.

2669
01:26:59,216 --> 01:27:01,356
- Don't cheer for me.
- That's it.

2670
01:27:01,756 --> 01:27:04,226
- The next player. Se Yoon.
- Five, four,

2671
01:27:04,326 --> 01:27:06,465
- three, two, one.
- Three, two, one.

2672
01:27:06,466 --> 01:27:08,025
- Okay. Good.
- Move over.

2673
01:27:08,026 --> 01:27:09,125
- Move over.
- Here.

2674
01:27:09,126 --> 01:27:10,536
- Hurry and move over.
- Wash this.

2675
01:27:11,596 --> 01:27:14,305
(Seon Ho wants to finish cleaning the webfoot octopuses.)

2676
01:27:14,306 --> 01:27:16,436
Let me take care of it. I'll do it.

2677
01:27:16,506 --> 01:27:17,746
Parboil them and separate them.

2678
01:27:18,476 --> 01:27:21,706
Seon Ho seems to have basic cooking knowledge.

2679
01:27:21,906 --> 01:27:23,075
(Perfect)

2680
01:27:23,076 --> 01:27:24,176
You did well.

2681
01:27:24,646 --> 01:27:26,376
- Is this good enough?
- Okay.

2682
01:27:26,746 --> 01:27:27,985
(The youngest, Seon Ho's skillful touch)

2683
01:27:27,986 --> 01:27:30,086
- Put them in here.
- Should I parboil them now?

2684
01:27:30,186 --> 01:27:32,715
- Go.
- Tell me when to take them out.

2685
01:27:32,716 --> 01:27:33,725
(Parboil the webfoot octopuses slightly in boiling water.)

2686
01:27:33,726 --> 01:27:35,756
- This is too many.
- It's okay. Put them all in.

2687
01:27:36,856 --> 01:27:39,966
(Seasonal webfoot octopus legs are parboiled to a milky white.)

2688
01:27:39,996 --> 01:27:42,225
Try the broth again.

2689
01:27:42,226 --> 01:27:44,996
This isn't easy. It's not easy to make.

2690
01:27:46,396 --> 01:27:49,106
(The Manila clam broth has steeped nicely to a milky white.)

2691
01:27:49,236 --> 01:27:50,536
Try it. It's good.

2692
01:27:51,606 --> 01:27:52,636
It's a little...

2693
01:27:52,906 --> 01:27:55,345
It's a little too salty.

2694
01:27:55,346 --> 01:27:57,515
It should be salty. We will put noodles in it.

2695
01:27:57,516 --> 01:27:59,176
- That's right.
- I told you it was good.

2696
01:27:59,276 --> 01:28:01,385
- The pen shell.
- Watch your fingers.

2697
01:28:01,386 --> 01:28:03,186
Watch your fingers. It breaks easily.

2698
01:28:03,216 --> 01:28:04,316
- Here?
- Yes.

2699
01:28:04,456 --> 01:28:06,315
Cut it open slowly. The meat is placed here.

2700
01:28:06,316 --> 01:28:07,556
You can open it slowly.

2701
01:28:07,786 --> 01:28:10,125
- This is harder than I thought.
- It's not easy.

2702
01:28:10,126 --> 01:28:12,195
The meat is attached in the middle.

2703
01:28:12,196 --> 01:28:14,196
- What are you doing, Se Yoon?
- Good.

2704
01:28:15,526 --> 01:28:17,595
It's done. Good job.

2705
01:28:17,596 --> 01:28:20,236
- It's done.
- Just take the adductor muscle.

2706
01:28:21,006 --> 01:28:22,765
(Chef Ho Young came to take a look at the shell.)

2707
01:28:22,766 --> 01:28:24,035
The pen shell looks nice.

2708
01:28:24,036 --> 01:28:25,805
- It's huge.
- It's amazing.

2709
01:28:25,806 --> 01:28:27,105
- It's done. Good.
- My goodness.

2710
01:28:27,106 --> 01:28:29,626
- Separate the adductor muscle now.
- Only the adductor muscle.

2711
01:28:30,016 --> 01:28:31,215
Is a pen shell this big?

2712
01:28:31,216 --> 01:28:32,815
- Sure.
- Yes. The shell is so big.

2713
01:28:32,816 --> 01:28:35,316
All right. Ten seconds.

2714
01:28:36,416 --> 01:28:38,386
Ten seconds.

2715
01:28:40,926 --> 01:28:42,556
(Ho Young is warming up.)

2716
01:28:43,196 --> 01:28:45,726
I will suppress Sam Kim's remaining spirit.

2717
01:28:45,826 --> 01:28:46,866
Let's go!

2718
01:28:47,626 --> 01:28:50,096
Three, two, one.

2719
01:28:50,196 --> 01:28:51,336
The chefs enter.

2720
01:28:51,796 --> 01:28:53,535
Instead of sweet and salty dishes,

2721
01:28:53,536 --> 01:28:56,466
I will win with the natural flavors of the ingredients.

2722
01:28:57,176 --> 01:28:58,975
(Chef Jung Ho Young, Chef Sam Kim)

2723
01:28:58,976 --> 01:29:00,276
Let's go, Chef!

2724
01:29:01,206 --> 01:29:03,846
(Sam Kim cannot beat me today again.)

2725
01:29:03,976 --> 01:29:06,115
Hey, let's watch his performance.

2726
01:29:06,116 --> 01:29:07,145
Okay.

2727
01:29:07,146 --> 01:29:09,145
- My goodness. That's cool.
- I did a lot of work, right?

2728
01:29:09,146 --> 01:29:11,486
- My goodness.
- Let's go, Black and White.

2729
01:29:12,416 --> 01:29:14,625
(Braised silver pomfret and radish)

2730
01:29:14,626 --> 01:29:15,986
- Cheer for him.
- Hey.

2731
01:29:16,086 --> 01:29:17,525
- Ho Young Keu Keu - Ho Young Keu Keu

2732
01:29:17,526 --> 01:29:19,096
(Livening up the mood with cheering)

2733
01:29:20,396 --> 01:29:22,365
(He looks like a pro even when draining water.)

2734
01:29:22,366 --> 01:29:24,286
He just put it in like that? Without cutting it?

2735
01:29:24,396 --> 01:29:25,795
- Did he already do it?
- I did.

2736
01:29:25,796 --> 01:29:27,136
He finished preparing it already.

2737
01:29:27,206 --> 01:29:28,646
- What's that?
- What are you doing?

2738
01:29:28,936 --> 01:29:31,835
- Cooking wine.
- He's adding something sweet!

2739
01:29:31,836 --> 01:29:32,906
It's a cooking wine.

2740
01:29:33,036 --> 01:29:35,076
He can't cook without it.

2741
01:29:36,246 --> 01:29:37,716
What are you adding now?

2742
